From Gordon Sasamori Subject Re viewing postscript files under X windows In C tGoJ J inmet camb inmet com George Snyder writes In article sk rINN Kin Cho writes I wonder if anybody know of a X window based postscript file viewer that runs under SunOS prefered , HPUX, or IBM AIX If you are running Sun OpenWindows, you can use pageview This is an X Window PostScript previewer like ghostview , but displays much nicer Yes, but it's broken on OW It does not handle multiple pages well If you don't have the proper PostScript commands it will draw the entire document on the same page instead of pausing after each page I haven't tried OW yet, though v v v v v v v Gordon T Sasamori HC CSIC MCU Design email , Nippon Motorola Ltd voice , FAX